
[1]deceased

   DECE'ASED, pp. or a. Departed from life. This is used as a passive
   participle. He is deceased, for he has deceased; he was deceased, for
   he had deceased. This use of the participle of an intransitive verb is
   not infrequent, but the word omitted is really has. He has deceased. It
   is properly an adjective, like dead.

   DECE'ASING, ppr. Departing from life; dying.

   DECE'DENT, n. A deceased person.

